==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ablactation
<hw>Ab`lac*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The weaning of a child from the breast, or of young beasts from
their dam.</def> <rj><au>Blount.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Hort.)</fld> <def>The process of grafting now
called <altname>inarching</altname>, or <altname>grafting by
approach</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ablaqueate</ent>⟦br⟧
